tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE warranty_information (
  part_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  part_name VARCHAR(255),
  service_provider VARCHAR(255),
  warranty_duration INT,
  warranty_start_date DATE,
  warranty_end_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE parts_warranty (
  part_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  part_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  warranty_start_date DATE NOT NULL,
  warranty_end_date DATE NOT NULL,
  service_provided TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE service_records (
  record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  part_id INT REFERENCES parts_warranty(part_id),
  service_date DATE NOT NULL,
  service_provider VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  service_description TEXT,
  claim_status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE warranty_claims (
    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    claim_date DATE,
    part_id INT REFERENCES parts(part_id),
    service_id INT REFERENCES services(service_id),
    claim_status VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE WarrantyInfo (
    warranty_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    part_id UUID REFERENCES Parts(part_id),
    service_id UUID REFERENCES Services(service_id),
    warranty_start_date DATE,
    warranty_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Claims (
    claim_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    warranty_id UUID REFERENCES WarrantyInfo(warranty_id),
    claim_date DATE,
    claim_description STRING,
    claim_resolved BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE parts (
    part_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    part_name VARCHAR(255),
    supplier_id INT,
    warranty_info VARCHAR(500)
)

CREATE TABLE suppliers (
    supplier_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supplier_name VARCHAR(255),
    supplier_address VARCHAR(255),
    contact_person VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE services (
    service_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    service_name VARCHAR(255),
    service_description VARCHAR(500),
    cost DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE warranty_claims (
    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    part_id INT,
    service_id INT,
    claim_status VARCHAR(50),
    claim_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE warranty_compliance (
    compliance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supplier_id INT,
    part_id INT,
    compliance_status VARCHAR(50),
    last_checked TIMESTAMP
)
